text: Bugulchan () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Leninsky Selsoviet, Kuyurgazinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 582 as of 2010. There are 11 streets. == Geography == It is located 24 km from Yermolayevo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Kuyurgazinsky District
title: Bugulchan
